<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,1012,1796]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1301,1327]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Remarks.</emphasis>
In the specimens loaned from the NHM, 10–11 pairs of the pseudanal setae and 10–22 of the peripheral setae situated postero-laterally are present (as in the original description of the species in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hirst, A. S." box="[1205,1325,1337,1363]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="136 - 143" refId="ref71093" refString="Hirst, A. S. (1917) On some new mites living on lizards. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 8, 136 - 143. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931709486917" type="journal article" year="1917">Hirst 1917</bibRefCitation>
) vs. presence of 6–9 pairs of the pseudanal setae and 15–16 pairs of the peripheral setae situated postero-laterally according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Jack, K. M." box="[180,344,1409,1436]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="261 - 295" refId="ref71388" refString="Jack, K. M. (1962 b) Observations on the genus Pterygosoma (Acari: Pterygosomatidae). Parasitology, 52, 261 - 295. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0031182000027177" type="journal article" year="1962">Jack’s (1962b)</bibRefCitation>
redescription.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,1012,1796]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Furthermore, in accordance with Article 75.3 of the International Code of Zoological Nomenclature (ICZN 1999, 2012) I designate one of the female specimens from the NHM as a 
<typeStatus box="[988,1077,1482,1508]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">neotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hirst, 1917" authorityName="Hirst" authorityYear="1917" class="Arachnida" family="Pterygosomatidae" genus="Pterygosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[1116,1365,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Pterygosoma persicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hirst, A. S." pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="136 - 143" refId="ref71093" refString="Hirst, A. S. (1917) On some new mites living on lizards. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 8, 136 - 143. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931709486917" type="journal article" year="1917">Hirst, 1917</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with the purpose of clarifying the taxonomic status of the species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hirst" authorityYear="1917" box="[944,1063,1518,1543]" class="Arachnida" family="Pterygosomatidae" genus="Pterygosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[944,1063,1518,1543]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">P. persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hirst, A. S." pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="136 - 143" refId="ref71093" refString="Hirst, A. S. (1917) On some new mites living on lizards. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 8, 136 - 143. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931709486917" type="journal article" year="1917">Hirst (1917)</bibRefCitation>
and later illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hirst, A. S." box="[487,628,1553,1580]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="173 - 200" refId="ref71133" refString="Hirst, A. S. (1926) On the parasitic mites of the suborder Prostigmata (Trombidioidea) found on lizards. Linnean Society Journal, Zoology, 36, 173 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1926. tb 02169. x" type="journal article" year="1926">Hirst (1926)</bibRefCitation>
. To my knowledge, none of the original type series of Hirst’s collection are extant. However, based on Hirst’s type specimens and newly collected mites 
<bibRefCitation author="Jack, K. M." box="[1059,1204,1589,1616]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="261 - 295" refId="ref71388" refString="Jack, K. M. (1962 b) Observations on the genus Pterygosoma (Acari: Pterygosomatidae). Parasitology, 52, 261 - 295. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0031182000027177" type="journal article" year="1962">Jack (1962b)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed the species, described male and protonymph, and provided data about new localities. For these reasons the specimen is suitable for designation as the 
<typeStatus box="[493,585,1662,1688]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">neotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,1012,1796]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="NHM" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="neotype">
Based on the close morphological similarity of the specimen loaned from 
<collectionCode box="[1022,1087,1698,1724]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">NHM</collectionCode>
from the type locality and type host to the original description of the species (
<bibRefCitation author="Hirst, A. S." box="[659,783,1733,1759]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="136 - 143" refId="ref71093" refString="Hirst, A. S. (1917) On some new mites living on lizards. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 8, 136 - 143. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931709486917" type="journal article" year="1917">Hirst 1917</bibRefCitation>
), I designate a 
<typeStatus box="[947,1036,1734,1760]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">neotype</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode box="[1049,1116,1733,1759]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">NHM</collectionCode>
no. 1966.2.22.851–860) and present a redescription of the species above
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
